section.section:
"Primary law enforcement officer" means:
In a municipal corporation, the chief of police, if any, or the chief's designee;
In a county that has a county police department, the chief of police or the chief's designee;
In a county without a police department, the sheriff or the sheriff's designee;
In Baltimore City, the Police Commissioner or the Police Commissioner's designee;
The Secretary of State Police; or
The principal law enforcement officers of a federal law enforcement agency or the officer's designee.
